## 2026-03-27 - PreviewPanel resolveValue: shadow/typography composite token values produce [object Object]
- Added `formatCompositeValue()` helper that formats structured DTCG objects into CSS strings: dimension `{value,unit}` → `"16px"`, shadow `{offsetX,offsetY,blur,spread,color}` → `"2px 4px 8px 0 #000"`, typography `{fontFamily,fontSize,fontWeight,lineHeight}` → `"600 16px/1.5 Inter"`.
- Also handles arrays of shadows (→ comma-separated) for multi-layer shadow tokens.
- Refactored `resolveValue` to delegate to `formatCompositeValue` for all object/array values before falling through to `String()`.

