## 2026-03-27 - Set name validation rejects `/` but UI expects folder-structured names
- Updated validation regex from `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+$` to `^[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+(?:\/[a-zA-Z0-9_-]+)*$` in 5 locations (2 in sets.ts routes, 3 in token-store.ts methods).
- Updated token-store file I/O to support subdirectory storage: `_createSetNoRebuild` and `saveSet` now `mkdir -p` parent dirs; `listTokenFiles` walks subdirs recursively; file watcher uses `**/*.tokens.json` glob; `deleteSet` and `renameSet` clean up empty parent dirs.
- Added `encodeURIComponent()` around set name variables in ~27 API URL templates across App.tsx and 8 component/hook files to ensure `/` in names is properly escaped in URL paths.

